The ColorPresenter renders output using a Theme — a mapping from 14 named elements to Style values. Each element represents a distinct visual category: marker_id, spec_id, filepath, line_number, hash, status_ok, status_warn, status_error, section_header, command, hint, diff_add, diff_remove, diff_hunk. A Style composes ANSI attributes: a Color SGR parameter (e.g. "92" for bright green, "38;5;37" for 256-color), a Bold flag, and a Dim flag. Style.Apply(s) wraps s in the composed ANSI sequence; a zero-value Style returns s unchanged. The <ref spec="output.guardrail_property">guardrail property</ref> holds for every theme because Apply only wraps text in ANSI codes — it never changes the text content. See <ref spec="output_intent.themable_output">themable output</ref> and <ref spec="output_impl.theme_types">theme types</ref>.